# Installing ANTLR to run with Python

**Install Maven**

    sudo apt-get install maven

**Download jar file**

    cd /usr/local/lib
    curl -O http://www.antlr.org/download/antlr-4.7.1-complete.jar

**Add antlr4 to your class path.**

    export CLASSPATH=".:/usr/local/lib/antlr-4.7.1-complete.jar:$CLASSPATH"

**Create alias**

    alias antlr4='java -Xmx500M -cp "/usr/local/lib/antlr-4.7.1-complete.jar:$CLASSPATH" org.antlr.v4.Tool'
    alias grun='java org.antlr.v4.gui.TestRig'

**Test install**

    java org.antlr.v4.Tool

**Add to bashrc**

    export CLASSPATH=".:/usr/local/lib/antlr-4.7.1-complete.jar:$CLASSPATH"
    alias antlr4='java -Xmx500M -cp "/usr/local/lib/antlr-4.7.1-complete.jar:$CLASSPATH" org.antlr.v4.Tool'
    # alias grun='java org.antlr.v4.runtime.misc.TestRig'
	alias grun='java org.antlr.v4.gui.TestRig'
	alias antlr4py3='java -Xmx500M -cp "/usr/local/lib/antlr-4.7.1-complete.jar:$CLASSPATH" org.antlr.v4.Tool -Dlanguage=Python3'
	alias antlr4py2='java -Xmx500M -cp "/usr/local/lib/antlr-4.7.1-complete.jar:$CLASSPATH" org.antlr.v4.Tool -Dlanguage=Python2'
	alias antlr4vpy3='java -Xmx500M -cp "/usr/local/lib/antlr-4.7.1-complete.jar:$CLASSPATH" org.antlr.v4.Tool -Dlanguage=Python3 -no-listener -visitor'
	alias antlr4vpy2='java -Xmx500M -cp "/usr/local/lib/antlr-4.7.1-complete.jar:$CLASSPATH" org.antlr.v4.Tool -Dlanguage=Python2 -no-listener -visitor'
	alias pygrun='python3 /opt/antlr/antlr4/runtime/Python3/bin/pygrun'

**Install runtime**

    sudo pip install antlr4-python3-runtime
    sudo pip3 install antlr4-python3-runtime
    sudo pip install antlr4-python2-runtime

**Install dependencies**

    sudo pip3 install typing
    sudo pip2 install typing

***Python target***

Python target support for ANTLR landed in version 4.4.
In this short writeup, I would like to document the installation process.


    mkdir -p /opt/antlr
    cd /opt/antlr
    git clone git@github.com:parrt/antlr4.git

add the corresponding libraries from the site:

    https://github.com/antlr/antlr4/blob/master/doc/python-target.md
    https://pypi.python.org/pypi/antlr4-python2-runtime/
    https://pypi.python.org/pypi/antlr4-python3-runtime/

then

    cd antlr4
    export MAVEN_OPTS="-Xmx1G"
    mvn clean
    mvn -DskipTests install

    ./bild.py mkjar

    cd /opt/antlr/antlr4-python3
    sudo python3 setup.py install

    antlr4 -Dlanguage=Python3 Hello.g4

    python3 execute.py hello-me

**Check version (open terminal)**

    antlr4

Once installed, navigate to folder, specify the language to use, along with the grammar file name
it will generate files to use

    antlr4 -Dlanguage=Python3 Hello.g4


**Grun with java**

    antlr4 Hello.g4
    javac *.java
    grun Hello r -gui input.txt


